---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="About — Zahiruddin Tavargere" description="Senior GenAI Architect at Dell, YouTuber, and community builder passionate about AI agents.">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-page">
      <div class="about-header">
        <div class="chip">The Expert</div>
        <h1>Zahiruddin Tavargere</h1>
        <p class="title-line">Senior Principal Engineer & GenAI Architect @ Dell · Bengaluru, India</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-body prose">
        <h2>My Story</h2>
        <p>I'm a firm believer in social learning. I owe my dev career to all the tech content creators I learned from — agentexpert.io is my contribution back to the community.</p>
        <p>After 15+ years of building distributed systems, automation tools, and designing software architecture, I was tasked to lead a GenAI team at Dell. That forced me to step out of my comfort zone and adapt — just as I always have. Within 3 months I had transitioned into an AI Engineer, and I've been deep in the agent-building world ever since.</p>
        <h2>What I Do</h2>
        <p>At Dell Technologies, I work as a Senior Principal Engineer & Generative AI Architect, building AI Acceleration Platform solutions. I've won the Dell AI Hackathon (2017), Quality Hackout (2018), and Cloud IT Hackathon (2016).</p>
        <p>Outside Dell, I run the <strong>Adaptive Engineer</strong> brand — a YouTube channel, Substack newsletter, and blog focused on helping software engineers adapt to the AI era.</p>
        <h2>Why agentexpert.io</h2>
        <p>There's a lot of AI content out there. Most of it is surface-level, hype-driven, or written by people who haven't shipped real agents. This site is different — everything here is grounded in actual implementation experience, real production challenges, and honest learnings.</p>
        <p>My goal: give you the structured knowledge to go from curious to confident in building AI agents.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="links-grid">
        <a href="https://youtube.com/@adaptiveengineer" target="_blank" class="profile-link">▶ YouTube — Adaptive Engineer</a>
        <a href="https://newsletter.adaptiveengineer.com" target="_blank" class="profile-link">✉ Newsletter — The Adaptive Engineer</a>
        <a href="https://zahere.com" target="_blank" class="profile-link">✍ Blog — zahere.com</a>
        <a href="https://twitter.com/zahiruddin_t" target="_blank" class="profile-link">𝕏 Twitter — @zahiruddin_t</a>
        <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/zahiruddin-tavargere" target="_blank" class="profile-link">in LinkedIn</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-page { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 5rem 0; }
  .about-header { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  .chip { display: inline-block; padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem; background: rgba(0,255,136,0.1); border: 1px solid rgba(0,255,136,0.2); color: var(--accent); border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.75rem; font-family: var(--font-mono); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem); font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .title-line { color: var(--muted); font-size: 1rem; }
  .about-body { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  .links-grid { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; }
  .profile-link { display: block; padding: 1rem 1.5rem; background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 10px; text-decoration: none; color: var(--text); font-weight: 600; transition: border-color 0.2s, color 0.2s; }
  .profile-link:hover { border-color: var(--accent); color: var(--accent); }
</style>
